\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 \ul \ulc0 Introduction
\f1\b0 \ulnone \
Hello! This document contains important information about the code used for data analysis for the \'93Reproductive stages in low bush blueberry (
\f2\i Vaccinium angustifolium
\f1\i0 ) occur earlier with increasing temperature\'94 paper. The code follows the steps provided in the statistical analysis section of the paper. Please start at folder one (1 - Initial Data Cleaning) and proceed to folder two (2 - Removing Outliers), etc.  All code was created in R 4.4.1 and run in Rstudio 2024.04.2+764. \
\

\f0\b \ul Notes
\f1\b0 \ulnone \
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	
\f3 \uc0\u9642 
\f1 	}Fruit post-veraison and seed disperse are synonymous. Fruit post-veraison was used in the paper but seed disperse was used in the code.\
{\listtext	
\f3 \uc0\u9642 
\f1 	}Ecoregion and ecozone are synonymous. Ecoregion was used in the paper but ecozone was used in the code.\
